cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the use of algorithms for decision-making, particularly for predictions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on interpretability and simplicity of prediction functions suggests a connection to the field of computational complexity (cs.CY). The discussion of equity and fairness in decision-making connects to the subfield of cryptography (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
